<Content>Room with a view Just spent two fabulous nights at the Arts with a 17th floor deluxe room. The room was immaculate with beautiful furnishings and a spectacular view over Port Olympic ... watching the sunrise over the med from the comfort of your bed is just something else.We travelled with our two children aged 9 and 5. The room had two queen size beds and was perfectly equipt with all requirements. The bathroom was stunning with double sinks, marble bath, separate toilet and amazing shower room. The hotel is truly beautiful and the flower arrangements and Christmas decorations were gorgeous. The staff were extremely attentive. My children particulary loved the 'Cookie Man' who greeted our return to the hotel one evening with a tray of the most delicious cookies.Booked this break for my 40th birthday through lastminute.com and got a really good deal.We have visited Barcelona on a number of occasions so were aware that the Arts is a good 30+ minute walk to the centre. If you want a cheaper family room in the centre of Barcelona try the Tryp Apolo. If you want luxury and enjoy a walk along the beach with good restaurants on your doorstep, look no further than the Arts.We didn't eat in the hotel so can't comment on the food. Barcelona is my favourite destination and having been in both January and December this year, it is the perfect winter city break. This weekend saw clear blue skies with a pleasant temperature of 20 degrees.Love Barca, love The Arts .... enjoy 
